  "ciliary_role": "Downregulated in diseases associated with ciliopathies, including BBS, PKD and PHP. Regulates multiciliogenesis and differenciation of ciliated cells by phosphorylating MARK3 which supresses ERK1/2 (31636950). Required for CCL2 regulation within cilia, via interactions with NPHP1, ANKS3 and NEK7 (29925518). Bending of cilium activates Lkb1 pathway, which inhibits mTORC1 activity and regulation cell size (20972424). Duct-specific deletion causes duct dilations and shorter cilia with swollen tips, indicative of perturbed intraciliary transport (28159992).",
